{"info": {"author": "Will Breaden Madden", "author_email": "wbm@protonmail.ch", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": [], "description": "stream\\_monitor\n===============\n\nThis program monitors a specified set of data streams (files) for\nchanges. If a file is not changed in a specified time, an alert is sent\nusing `scalar <https://github.com/wdbm/scalar>`__.\n\nsetup\n=====\n\n.. code:: bash\n\n    pip install stream_monitor\n\nSet up scalar, as described `here <https://github.com/wdbm/scalar>`__.\n\nconfiguration and usage\n=======================\n\nA JSON configuration file (by default\n``stream_monitor_configuration.json``) guides the program on the streams\nto monitor and their required update times. Its contents are of the\nfollowing form:\n\n.. code:: python\n\n    {\n        \"streams\": {\n            \"./recording.csv\": {\"update_time\"}: 30\n        }\n    }\n\nIn this example configuration, ``recording.csv`` is a filepath to\nmonitor for changes and ``30`` is the time in seconds within which the\nfilepath should change.\n\nWhen the program ``stream_monitor`` is executed, it imports the\nconfiguration and runs in a continuous loop, sending an alert whenever\nit detects that a stream is not being updated in its expected update\ntime. The script has options for the configuration filepath, alarms,\nchecking interval and verbosity (see ``stream_monitor --help``).\n", "description_content_type": "", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/wdbm/stream_monitor", "keywords": "", "license": "GPLv3", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "stream_monitor", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/stream_monitor/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/stream_monitor/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/wdbm/stream_monitor"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/stream_monitor/2018.8.26.1543/", "requires_dist": null, "requires_python": "", "summary": "monitoring and alerting program for data streams such as recording files that update regularly", "version": "2018.8.26.1543", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <div id=\"stream-monitor\">\n<h2>stream_monitor</h2>\n<p>This program monitors a specified set of data streams (files) for\nchanges. If a file is not changed in a specified time, an alert is sent\nusing <a href=\"https://github.com/wdbm/scalar\" rel=\"nofollow\">scalar</a>.</p>\n</div>\n<div id=\"setup\">\n<h2>setup</h2>\n<pre>pip install stream_monitor\n</pre>\n<p>Set up scalar, as described <a href=\"https://github.com/wdbm/scalar\" rel=\"nofollow\">here</a>.</p>\n</div>\n<div id=\"configuration-and-usage\">\n<h2>configuration and usage</h2>\n<p>A JSON configuration file (by default\n<tt>stream_monitor_configuration.json</tt>) guides the program on the streams\nto monitor and their required update times. Its contents are of the\nfollowing form:</p>\n<pre><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"s2\">\"streams\"</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span>\n        <span class=\"s2\">\"./recording.csv\"</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"s2\">\"update_time\"</span><span class=\"p\">}:</span> <span class=\"mi\">30</span>\n    <span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</pre>\n<p>In this example configuration, <tt>recording.csv</tt> is a filepath to\nmonitor for changes and <tt>30</tt> is the time in seconds within which the\nfilepath should change.</p>\n<p>When the program <tt>stream_monitor</tt> is executed, it imports the\nconfiguration and runs in a continuous loop, sending an alert whenever\nit detects that a stream is not being updated in its expected update\ntime. The script has options for the configuration filepath, alarms,\nchecking interval and verbosity (see <tt>stream_monitor <span class=\"pre\">--help</span></tt>).</p>\n</div>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 4208594, "releases": {"2018.1.11.1552": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "3bcfa9448c8a4bbfaf7077a623e8f582", "sha256": "c2104252d97220a097e1e0ec5420ed611fee51147d3273aa3aadba43d90ab4e3"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "stream_monitor-2018.1.11.1552.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "3bcfa9448c8a4bbfaf7077a623e8f582", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": null, "size": 2592, "upload_time": "2018-01-11T15:57:36", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2018-01-11T15:57:36.406226Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/96/57/1a0b66c3adeb9c86fc96ab4e29c1869c647c706cf9648f259599f9b928c9/stream_monitor-2018.1.11.1552.tar.gz", "yanked": false}], "2018.1.11.1609": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "ff8daabf00a2b133dfa75ef78ee82cfc", "sha256": "ee84865afbac6790d612df937bb5a19e710f8d9350f05cd3091dc479abbf0d5e"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "stream_monitor-2018.1.11.1609.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "ff8daabf00a2b133dfa75ef78ee82cfc", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": null, "size": 2824, "upload_time": "2018-01-11T16:10:12", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2018-01-11T16:10:12.691751Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/8c/58/202f0a39b3629751182abddbf0d5a5dd3a1411fabdee629bc293711e8186/stream_monitor-2018.1.11.1609.tar.gz", "yanked": false}], "2018.1.22.115": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "3a7776473597f733a5e2156abaee76bb", "sha256": "bdc7f1d90e3031dc35b8a062c91f21fe2dd2579eda9d41030bfdd2b59b7741f8"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "stream_monitor-2018.1.22.115.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "3a7776473597f733a5e2156abaee76bb", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": null, "size": 2871, "upload_time": "2018-01-22T01:17:09", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2018-01-22T01:17:09.141427Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/74/a5/454bdbbfd873b35cfba53b957c7052915da8220f2ed670eec968c3db6887/stream_mo